### 4. The Ideal Unified Compatibility Report

If you force all these nuances into a simplistic CLI that just outputs `Compatible: False`, developers will ignore the tool. The ideal report must serve the CI/CD policy engine (which needs mathematical abstraction) while serving the human developer (who needs format-specific, actionable evidence).

The report should be a multi-dimensional matrix, grouping anomalies by **Tier** (Structural, Semantic, Usage).

